        "description": "# Privacy Policy\n\n**1. Controller**\n\nThe controller within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is:\n[Company name]\n[Address]\nPhone: [phone number]\nE-mail: [privacy e-mail or general e-mail]\nWeb: [domain]\n\n[Optional:] Data protection officer: [name/contact, if required].\n\n***\n\n**2. Purposes and legal bases**\n\nPersonal data is processed for the following purposes:\n- Providing and operating this website\n- Responding to enquiries\n- Preparing and performing contracts with customers and partners\n- Ensuring IT security and system stability.\n\nThe main legal bases are Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (contract / pre-contractual measures), Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interests, e.g. IT security) and, where required, Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent).\n\n***\n\n**3. Server log files**\n\nWhen you access our website, certain data is automatically processed and stored in server log files, e.g.:\n- IP address\n- Date and time of request\n- Requested URL\n- Referrer URL\n- Browser type and version\n- Operating system.\n\nProcessing is necessary for technical delivery of the website, IT security and administrative purposes (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR). Log data is deleted after [e.g. 7–30 days], unless longer storage is necessary for security reasons.\n\n***\n\n**4. Hosting and cloud services (e.g. AWS)**\n\nOur website is hosted by [hosting provider, e.g. Amazon Web Services EMEA SARL]. This may involve processing of personal data on servers located in the EU and, where configured, in third countries.\n\nWe have concluded a data processing agreement with the provider pursuant to Art. 28 GDPR.\nProcessing is based on our legitimate interests in a secure and efficient provision of our online services (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).\n\n[If third-country transfers (e.g. US) occur:]\nWhere data is transferred to a third country, this is based on appropriate safeguards pursuant to Art. 46 GDPR (e.g. EU Standard Contractual Clauses). Nevertheless, there may be an increased risk of access by authorities without effective legal remedies being available to you.\n\n***\n\n**5. Contacting us (e-mail / forms)**\n\nIf you contact us (e.g. by e-mail or via a contact form), the data you provide will be processed to handle your enquiry and any follow-up questions.\n\nThe legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (contract / pre-contractual measures) or Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (our legitimate interest in responding to enquiries). Data is deleted once your request has been processed and no statutory retention periods apply.\n\n***\n\n**6. Online appointment booking (optional, e.g. Calendly)**\n\nIf you book an appointment with us via an integrated scheduling tool (e.g. Calendly), the data you enter will be processed for the purpose of arranging and managing the appointment.\n\n- Service provider: [name, address, link to provider’s privacy policy]\n- Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (contract / pre-contractual measures).\nA data processing agreement pursuant to Art. 28 GDPR has been concluded.\nIf the provider transfers data to a third country (e.g. US), this is based on appropriate safeguards (e.g. EU Standard Contractual Clauses).\n\n***\n\n**7. Web analytics / tracking (only if used)**\n\nIf we use a web analytics tool (e.g. Google Analytics, Matomo, Plausible), it is activated only with your consent via our cookie banner (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR).\n\nDetails about the tool used (provider, functionality, storage period, opt-out options, third-country transfers) will be provided in the corresponding section. No analytics is carried out without your consent.\n\n***\n\n**8. Cookies and similar technologies**\n\nWe use only those cookies and similar technologies that are technically necessary for operating the website, or – for optional tools – only with your consent.\n\n- Technically necessary cookies: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interests)\n- Optional cookies / tools: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent).\n\nYou can withdraw your consent at any time with effect for the future via our cookie banner.\n\n***\n\n**9. Storage periods**\n\nUnless otherwise specified in this privacy policy, personal data is erased as soon as the purpose of processing has been fulfilled and no statutory retention obligations apply.\n\n***\n\n**10. Your rights**\n\nYou have the following rights under the GDPR with regard to your personal data:\n\n- Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)\n- Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)\n- Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)\n- Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)\n- Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)\n- Right to object to processing (Art. 21 GDPR).\n\nYou also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR).\nWhere processing is based on consent, you may withdraw your consent at any time with effect for the future (Art. 7(3) GDPR).\n\n***\n\n**11. Obligation to provide data**\n\nIf the provision of data is required for concluding or performing a contract or for our services, this will be indicated in the respective context. Without such data, we may not be able to conclude or perform the contract.\n\n***\n\n**12. Updates**\n\nThis privacy policy is currently valid and was last updated on [insert date].\nDue to further development of our website or changes in legal requirements, it may become necessary to amend this privacy policy.",
